Abstract

We analyze a dataset that contains the condition of the lower back pain of 310 persons (labelled Abnormal or Normal by trained physicians), collected along with some other physical spine details. Our goal is to identify which of those measurements might be important for predicting whether the pain in a personâs lower back is Abnormal or Normal, and how to predict that using various regression models. This html document created by R markdown contains the codes used in our group project.

First attempt: multiple logisitic regression models (full models)

cross_val <- function(data)
{
  df = data
  auc_vec = array(dim = 10)
  mis_vec = array(dim = 10)
  for(i in 1:10)
  {
    testid = sample(1:310,31,replace = FALSE)
    testdat = df[testid,]
    traindat = df[-testid,]
    fit = glm(condition~degree_spondylolisthesis + pelvic_radius + sacral_slope,
              data = traindat)
    testk = testdat[,1]
    testp = predict(fit,testdat)
    r <- roc(testk ~ testp)
    auc_vec[i]= auc(r)
    T = as.matrix(table(testp> 0.5, testk))
    misclass = (T[2,1] + T[2,1])/sum(T)
    mis_vec[i] = misclass
  }
  return(list("auc" =mean(auc_vec),"misclass" =mean(mis_vec)))
}

  geom_point(data = df2, aes(x = x, y = y), colour = "red", size = 3) +
  labs( y = "Std. Residuals", x = "Fitted Values")
}

myROC <- function(dat, train, logistic.fit,la){
  train.pred <- predict(logistic.fit, dat[train, ])
  train.known <- dat[train, ]$condition
  test.pred <- predict(logistic.fit, dat[-train, ])
  test.known <- dat[-train, ]$condition
  library(pROC)
  train_roc = roc(train.known ~ train.pred, plot = TRUE, col = "red")
  test_roc = roc(test.known ~ test.pred, plot = TRUE, add = TRUE, col = "blue")
  legend("bottomright", legend = c(paste("train_AUC = ", round(auc(train_roc), 2)), 
                                   paste("test_AUC = ", round(auc(test_roc), 2))), 
         fill = c(2, 4), bty = "n",title = la)
}

(Linear or Quadratic) Discriminant Analysis

Discriminant.Analysis<-function(Data){
  train = sample(nrow(Data), round(nrow(Data)/2), replace = F) # selects training data
  lda.fit = lda(condition ~ ., data = Data, subset = train)
  train.lda = predict(lda.fit, Data[train,])
  test.lda = predict(lda.fit, Data[-train,])
  l1 <- mean(train.lda$class != Data$condition[train]) 
  # proportions of misclassification for LDA on train data
  l2 <- mean(test.lda$class != Data$condition[-train]) 
  # proportions of misclassification for LDA on test data
  qda.fit = qda(condition ~ ., data = Data, subset = train)
  train.qda = predict(qda.fit, Data[train,])
  test.qda = predict(qda.fit, Data[-train,])
  q1 <- mean(train.qda$class != Data$condition[train]) 
  # proportions of misclassification for QDA on train data
  q2 <- mean(test.qda$class != Data$condition[-train]) 
  # proportions of misclassification for QDA on test data
    Mis <- matrix(c(l1, l2, q1, q2), ncol = 2, byrow = T)
    rownames(Mis) = c("LDA", "QDA"); colnames(Mis) = c("Train", "Test")
    return(Mis) # returns the proportions of misclassification
}

avg.misclass<-function(Data){
  # repeating the whole thing 20 times to get 
  # a better estimate of the proportion of misclassification
  Misclassification = matrix(0, nrow = 2, ncol = 2)
  for(i in 1:20) Misclassification = Misclassification + Discriminant.Analysis(Data)
# printing the percentages of misclassification, averaged over the 20 repetitions
  return(Misclassification/20 * 100)
}

Finding a smaller model: Subset selection

subset.select<-function(Response, Predictors, k){
  nothing <- glm(Response ~ 1 , family = binomial(logit), data = Predictors)
  full <- glm(Response ~ . , family = binomial(logit), data = Predictors)
  forwards <- step(nothing, scope = list(lower = formula(nothing), upper = formula(full)), 
                   direction = "forward", k = k, trace = 0)
  backwards <- step(full, scope = list(lower = formula(nothing), upper = formula(full)), 
                    direction = "backward", k = k, trace = 0)
  stepwise_n <- step(nothing, scope = list(lower=formula(nothing), upper = formula(full)), 
                     direction = "both", k = k, trace = 0)
  stepwise_f <- step(full, scope = list(lower=formula(nothing), upper = formula(full)), 
                     direction="both", k = k, trace = 0)
  ranks = matrix(c(forwards$rank, backwards$rank, stepwise_n$rank, stepwise_f$rank), 
                 nrow = 1)
  AIC.values = matrix(c(forwards$aic, backwards$aic, stepwise_n$aic, stepwise_f$aic), 
                      nrow = 1) - (2 - k) * ranks
  colnames(AIC.values) = c("forwards", "backwards", "step_nothing", "step_full")
  forwards.formula = summary(forwards)$call
  return(list(AIC.values, forwards.formula))
}

Next we compare them (Ridge, Lasso, Enet0.5) on the basis of misclassification error rates and auc (area under ROC curve) values.

compare.penreg<-function(type.meas){
  ridge.fit = glmnet(X, y, family = "binomial", alpha = 0)
  cv.ridge = cv.glmnet(X, y, family = "binomial", alpha = 0, nfolds = 10, type.measure = type.meas)
  s.ridge = cv.ridge$cvm[cv.ridge$lambda == cv.ridge$lambda.1se]
  lasso.fit = glmnet(X, y, family = "binomial", alpha = 1)
  cv.lasso = cv.glmnet(X, y, family = "binomial", alpha = 1, nfolds = 10, type.measure =  type.meas)
  s.lasso = cv.lasso$cvm[cv.lasso$lambda == cv.lasso$lambda.1se]
  enet.fit = glmnet(X, y, family = "binomial", alpha = 0.5)
  cv.enet = cv.glmnet(X, y, family = "binomial", alpha = 0.5, nfolds = 10, type.measure =  type.meas)
  s.enet = cv.enet$cvm[cv.enet$lambda == cv.enet$lambda.1se]

  Coefs = cbind(coef(cv.ridge, s = cv.ridge$lambda.1se), 
                coef(cv.lasso, s = cv.lasso$lambda.1se), 
                coef(cv.enet, s = cv.enet$lambda.1se))
  colnames(Coefs) = c("ridge", "lasso","enet0.5")
  print(Coefs[-2,])
  print(cbind(s.ridge, s.lasso, s.enet))

  plot(log(cv.lasso$lambda), cv.lasso$cvm, ty = "l", lwd = 1.5, col="red", xlab="log(Lambda)", ylab=cv.lasso$name)
  points(x = log(cv.lasso$lambda.1se), y = cv.lasso$cvm[cv.lasso$lambda == cv.lasso$lambda.1se], col = "red")
  lines(log(cv.enet$lambda), cv.enet$cvm, pch=19, lwd = 1.5, col="purple")
  points(x = log(cv.enet$lambda.1se), y = cv.enet$cvm[cv.enet$lambda == cv.enet$lambda.1se], col = "purple")
  lines(log(cv.ridge$lambda), cv.ridge$cvm, pch=19, lwd = 1.5, col="blue")
  points(x = log(cv.ridge$lambda.1se), y = cv.ridge$cvm[cv.ridge$lambda == cv.ridge$lambda.1se], col = "blue")
  if(type.meas == "auc")
    legend("bottomleft", legend=c("alpha = 1","alpha = 0.5","alpha = 0"), lwd = 1, pch = 1, col=c("red","purple","blue"))
  if(type.meas != "auc")
  legend("topleft", legend=c("alpha = 1","alpha = 0.5","alpha = 0"), lwd = 1, pch = 1, col=c("red","purple","blue"))
}
